<TITLE> 'Mugger' dies in hospital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 21 (bdnews24.com)An alleged mugger died in the Dhaka Medical College Hospital on Friday from fatal wounds he had suffered in mob beating in the capital. Officer-in-charge of Badda Police Station Kazi Wazed Ali said Sadek Ali, 22, and his three companions snatched Tk 5,500 at gunpoint from businessman 'Shaheen' at West Merul early in the morning. People chased them while he shouted for help, caught two and beat them. Ali died at around 3pm. Accomplice 'Shohag', 20, was also taken to the DMCH with critical wounds. The others involved in the mugging are 'Rony' and 'Babu' and all are residents of Hossain Market at Tongi, police added. 
